
  AZ - 	Each availability zone (AZ) is one or more
	discrete data centers with redundant power,
	networking, and connectivity
	• They’re separate from each other, so that
	they’re isolated from disasters
	• They’re connected with high bandwidth,
	ultra-low latency networking
	
  Access Key ID ~= username
  • Secret Access Key ~= password
  
  Elastic IP - 
  When you stop and then start an EC2 instance, it can change its public IP.
  • If you need to have a fixed public IP for your instance, you need an
  Elastic IP
  • An Elastic IP is a public IPv4 IP you own as long as you don’t delete it
  • You can attach it to one instance at a time.
  
  Cloudwatch alarms is kind of alarm that will trigger the asg based on conditions like 
  when cpu usage > 70% then add 2 instances.
  
  Note all AWS services focuses on high availability,scalability and high performance,security.
  
  Route 53 is DNS service.
  
  CloudWatch for monitoring metrics.		

  AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service that allows you to run code without provisioning or managing servers.
  It executes code in response to events and automatically manages the underlying compute resources. 
  Lambda functions are ideal for event-driven applications, such as processing data from S3 buckets or responding to HTTP requests. 

